latestPosts.caption:
The campus has meant a lot of things, to all of us. It is not merely a place, it is the place we still call home.

We have all left it behind, moved ahead in our lives and careers. and yet, whenever and wherever there is a congregation which comprises us, in any number, our conversations go back to this place we call 'the campus'. 

The batch of 2020-22, we were on campus for a brief period of time, nevertheless, we made the best of every second spent there. Be it waiting for a friend to go to mess on the curving roads, or just walking to city lights, everyday...

And each time we went to that place, we just understood something. Some knot found itself untangled, and, we walked back simpler people. At peace.

At home.

A campus that will always be a home to our hearts. 

Lovely. Lavale. Louré. 

••••••••••

Shot this video with @vrunda_vachhani right after we reached the campus, 26 September 2021, and I was only able to edit it after 100s of reminders and curses from her. But now when I look at it, the time just feels right. It was meant to be this way. :P

Thoughts are beautifully penned down by Mr. @capnfuzzybeard in the caption. Finest storyteller in the lot. 

Music: Just Going by @ronnie_and_barty
